request.description:
**Create Blocked Sender Policy API**

**HTTP Request:**

- Method: POST

- URL: `https://api.services.mimecast.com/api/policy/blockedsenders/create-policy`

- Content-Type: application/json


**Request Body:**

- Structure: JSON object with a "data" array containing exactly 1 item.

- Each item in the "data" array must have:

    - "option" (required): A string that defines a policy action, must be one of: no_action, block_sender.

    - "policy" (required): A policy object with various parameters.


**Example Request Body:**

``` json
{
  "data": [
    {
      "option": "no_action",
      "policy": {
        "bidirectional": false,
        "comment": "This policy allows all senders without restrictions.",
        "conditions": {
          "headerFromDomain": "example.com",
          "subjectContains": "important",
          "messageSizeGreaterThanOrEqual": 5000
        },
        "description": "Allow all senders with certain conditions.",
        "enabled": true,
        "enforced": false,
        "from": {
          "fromPart": "header_from"
        },
        "to": {
          "toEternal": false
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

 ```

## webwhiteurl/delete-policy-with-targets

Deletes an existing Web Security Block or Allow List policy for domains or URLs.

**Endpoint**: `POST https://api.services.mimecast.com/api/policy/webwhiteurl/delete-policy-with-targets`

**Pre-requisites**:  
The role assigned to the app must have 'Web Security | Policies | Edit' permissions granted.

**Headers**:

- Content-Type: application/json


**Body Parameters**:

- `id`: (required) The Mimecast secure ID of an existing policy to be deleted.


**Request Body Example**:

``` json
{
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "policy-id-1"
    },
    {
      "id": "policy-id-2"
    }
    //... additional IDs as needed
  ]
}

 ```

## ttp/remediation/get-incident

Retrieves information about an existing remediation incident.

**Endpoint**: `POST https://api.services.mimecast.com/api/ttp/remediation/get-incident`

**Pre-requisites**:  
The role assigned to the app must have 'Services | Threat Remediation | Read' permissions granted.

**Headers**:

- Content-Type: application/json


**Body Parameters**:

- `id`: (Required) The Mimecast ID for a remediation incident.


**Request Body Example**:

``` json
{
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "incident-id-example"
    }
    // Additional incident IDs as needed (up to 25)
  ]
}

 ```

## ttp/remediation/search-hash

Identifies if an account has seen specific file hashes within messages over the last year.

**Endpoint**: `POST https://api.services.mimecast.com/api/ttp/remediation/search-hash`

**Pre-requisites**:  
The role assigned to the app must have 'Services | Threat Remediation | Read' permissions granted.

**Headers**:

- Content-Type: application/json


**Body Parameters**:

- `hashes`: (Required) Array of file hashes to check if they have been seen within an account.


**Request Body Example**:

``` json
{
  "data": [
    {
      "hashes": [
        "hash1",
        "hash2"
        // Additional hashes as needed (up to 100, but recommended no more than 20 per call)
      ]
    }
  ]
}

 ```

